law.text: The cabinet may contract with a governmental unit or other person, and a governmental unit may contract with the cabinet or any person in regard to the development of airports and other aeronautical matters.
law.history: Amended 1964 Ky. Acts ch. 134, sec. 16. -- Amended 1960 Ky. Acts ch. 179, sec. 67. -- Amended 1958 Ky. Acts ch. 153, sec. 47. -- Created 1948 Ky. Acts ch. 239, sec. 4.
